01:07.000 --> 01:08.600
SUSAN: And that's the news.

01:08.700 --> 01:13.600
But before we sign off, we'd like
to congratulate our very own Evan Baxter,

01:13.700 --> 01:17.500
who has just been elected
Buffalo's representative to Congress.

01:17.600 --> 01:18.900
And, now, we have a surprise for Evan.

01:19.000 --> 01:20.600
No, you don't.
We do.

01:20.600 --> 01:23.500
Oh, no. I really didn't expect this.

01:23.600 --> 01:25.800
Here's a look back at his run for office.

01:26.200 --> 01:27.600
(PEOPLE CHEERING)

01:28.500 --> 01:29.600
What are we gonna do?

01:29.700 --> 01:31.100
ALL: Change the world!

01:31.200 --> 01:32.200
That's right!

01:32.900 --> 01:34.400
(ALL CHEERING)

01:39.500 --> 01:41.500
ALL: Baxter! Baxter! Baxter!

01:48.500 --> 01:49.500
Hi.

01:49.600 --> 01:51.000
ALL: Baxter! Baxter!

01:51.000 --> 01:52.500
That's right!

01:54.700 --> 01:55.700
(CLEARING THROAT)

01:57.000 --> 02:01.200
I feel like that old Indian
in front of all the garbage.

02:02.700 --> 02:07.700
So, for the last time, this is Evan Baxter
for Eyewitness News. Good night.

02:08.400 --> 02:11.000
(HAVE YOU EVER SEEN THE RAIN PLAYING)

02:24.300 --> 02:27.500
GPS: Huntsville, Virginia.
Prestige Crest, four miles.

02:27.600 --> 02:29.100
What did we do before GPS?

02:29.200 --> 02:30.200
Nothing.

02:30.300 --> 02:32.500
Guys, Dad's very proud of his new car.

02:32.500 --> 02:37.200
Hey, I am proud of my new car.
Look, I'm a politician now.

02:37.200 --> 02:40.100
I'm in the public eye, and as you know,
when you are in the public eye,

02:40.200 --> 02:41.900
image is everything, isn't it?

02:46.900 --> 02:49.800
EVAN: Here it is! Welcome to the good life.

02:49.800 --> 02:53.200
Hey, guys, why the long faces?
We're off on a new adventure!

02:54.200 --> 02:56.400
It's just we're going to miss our friends.

02:56.400 --> 02:58.300
You'll make new friends, better friends.

02:58.300 --> 02:59.500
Yeah, richer friends.

02:59.600 --> 03:03.400
Do not mouth off to me, sir.
I am the boss of you.

03:03.500 --> 03:06.100
And let me tell you something,
you guys are gonna love this place.

03:06.700 --> 03:09.800
And you know what? I think there's
something for our fishermen up there.

03:11.000 --> 03:14.100
EVAN: Baxter family,
this is what's called a scenic vista.

03:14.200 --> 03:18.000
And I don't think the big man himself
could do a better job. Pretty cool, huh?

03:18.100 --> 03:19.900
Hey, Dad, an iguana can stay underwater
for 28 minutes.

03:20.000 --> 03:21.000
What's that?

03:21.100 --> 03:22.900
And a shrimp's heart is in its head.
Really?

03:23.000 --> 03:25.200
Okay, someone's had enough Animal Planet
for one lifetime.

03:25.300 --> 03:27.200
Yeah, let's head out! Come on.
The best is yet to come!

03:29.000 --> 03:31.700
EVAN: Gentlemen, I have saved
the best for last.

03:31.800 --> 03:35.300
Look over to the right.
That is your new home.

03:41.600 --> 03:42.600
RYAN: Whoa!

03:42.700 --> 03:43.900
JORDAN: That's our house?

03:44.000 --> 03:46.000
Uh-huh.
JOAN: I don't remember it being
this big in the brochure.

03:46.100 --> 03:47.400
Was it this big in the brochure?

03:47.500 --> 03:48.700
EVAN: Pretty amazing, isn't it?

03:48.800 --> 03:50.400
There they are!

03:51.900 --> 03:54.000
Is this curb appeal or what?

03:54.100 --> 03:55.600
Here we go!

03:55.700 --> 03:57.200
Honey, I think you're blocking my photo.

03:57.300 --> 03:58.300
Sorry.

03:58.400 --> 04:00.400
All right, everybody! Say "escrow"!

04:00.500 --> 04:02.300
ALL: Escrow!

04:03.500 --> 04:06.200
RYAN: Come on. Come on. Come on.
Come on. Go. Go. Go.

04:06.800 --> 04:08.700
EVAN: Guys, easy.

04:09.100 --> 04:10.600
(CHILDREN EXCLAIMING)

04:11.200 --> 04:12.300
This is our house?

04:12.400 --> 04:13.400
Uh-huh.

04:14.300 --> 04:15.500
MAN: Careful!

04:15.500 --> 04:17.399
JOAN: Honey, be careful!
EVAN: Watch it!

04:17.500 --> 04:18.600
Are you kidding me?

04:18.700 --> 04:19.899
Mom, can we go upstairs?
JOAN: Yep.

04:20.000 --> 04:21.399
And I get my own room, right?
Yep.

04:21.500 --> 04:22.900
(YELLING EXCITEDLY)

04:22.900 --> 04:25.500
Mr. Baxter, could you give us some
direction on these kitchen cabinets?

04:25.600 --> 04:26.600
Sure.

04:26.600 --> 04:31.200
Okay, it's between your maple
and your old-growth Brazilian cherry.

04:31.300 --> 04:33.200
That is nice! Which is best?

04:33.200 --> 04:36.300
Well, if you're not sensitive
to that "save the rainforest" stuff,

04:36.400 --> 04:37.800
you can't beat the Brazilian cherry.

04:37.900 --> 04:39.100
It's 200, 300 years old.

04:39.100 --> 04:40.700
Three hundred years.
Three hundred.

04:40.700 --> 04:42.300
Wow. That is old.

04:42.300 --> 04:44.600
And now you are going to hold my dishes.

04:44.700 --> 04:46.400
That's right. You going with the cherry?
Cheery cherry!

04:46.500 --> 04:48.000
Yeah. Definitely.
He's going with the cherry!

04:49.200 --> 04:50.300
RYAN: Dad, look!

04:50.400 --> 04:51.700
No, no, no!

04:51.700 --> 04:54.200
Ryan, do not touch him, please!

04:54.300 --> 04:55.800
Oh, no, no, no, no, get him away!

04:55.900 --> 04:58.200
No. He might have lice, fleas,
maggots or something.

04:58.200 --> 05:01.000
You do not play with stray dogs
because they are very...

05:01.100 --> 05:03.400
No, no! Get away, get away! Go!

05:04.100 --> 05:05.600
Okay. Oh, no, no, no.

05:05.700 --> 05:07.100
He's thirsty.
No, no, no.

05:07.200 --> 05:10.100
No, you don't! There we go.

05:10.100 --> 05:11.800
Well, Ryan, he's a stray.

05:11.800 --> 05:13.300
If we give him water,
he's just going to come back.

05:13.400 --> 05:16.900
Come on, Dad, why can't we keep him?
I mean, we've got a new house.

05:17.000 --> 05:18.900
Okay, Ryan, this is why we can't keep him.

05:19.000 --> 05:21.600
They are stinky. They are smelly.
They get hair all over the place.

05:21.700 --> 05:22.900
They get a little thing called the mange.

05:23.000 --> 05:26.000
In a nutshell, he is disgusting.
Case in point.

05:26.500 --> 05:28.400
(BOTH GIGGLING)

05:30.900 --> 05:34.200
EVAN: Ladies and gentlemen,
this concludes day one

05:34.300 --> 05:35.800
of the Baxters' new and exciting life.

05:35.900 --> 05:38.200
I have to do the new house dance.

05:38.300 --> 05:40.800
Wow! That dance?

05:40.900 --> 05:42.400
Mmm-hmm.
That's a good new house dance.

05:42.500 --> 05:43.800
Thank you.

05:43.800 --> 05:46.000
You know, those boys were having
so much fun tonight,

05:46.100 --> 05:48.100
I thought I would never get them to bed.

05:48.100 --> 05:52.800
And then Ryan did the cutest thing.
He asked if we could all pray together.

05:53.300 --> 05:55.900
Really? What did you pray about?

05:55.900 --> 05:58.000
He met a dog. What do you think
he prayed for?

05:58.100 --> 06:00.000
(EXCLAIMING IN DISGUST)

06:00.000 --> 06:02.800
Just a walking petri dish, that dog.

06:02.900 --> 06:05.100
And Jordan was very precise.

06:05.100 --> 06:08.900
He prayed for good visibility, good weather
on the hiking trip tomorrow.

06:09.000 --> 06:12.300
The hiking trip? Oh, right. Yeah.
The hiking trip. Yeah, yeah, yeah.

06:12.400 --> 06:14.300
You wanna know what I prayed for?

06:14.300 --> 06:16.200
Yeah. What did you pray for?

06:16.300 --> 06:19.400
I prayed we would become closer
as a family.

06:20.600 --> 06:25.100
Honey, you don't need to pray for that
to happen. I will make that happen.

06:25.100 --> 06:26.100
(SIGHING)

06:26.600 --> 06:28.300
What would you pray for?

06:28.300 --> 06:30.900
Me? I don't know. Praying just...

06:31.700 --> 06:32.700
(SIGHING)

06:32.800 --> 06:36.600
Honey, you're the one who said
you wanted to change the world.

06:37.100 --> 06:39.000
It's a pretty big job.

06:39.300 --> 06:41.600
If it were me,
I would take all the help I could get.

06:44.700 --> 06:47.100
(CROWD CHEERING)

06:47.200 --> 06:50.300
WOMAN OVER TV: Former Buffalo News
anchor, Evan Baxter, takes office tomorrow

06:50.400 --> 06:52.700
to make good on a lofty campaign promise.

06:52.800 --> 06:53.900
What are we going to do?

06:54.000 --> 06:55.300
ALL: Change the world!

06:55.300 --> 06:58.800
WOMAN OVER TV: Good luck, Congressman.
Many have tried, many have failed.

06:58.900 --> 07:00.100
Hello!

07:00.100 --> 07:02.000
This is Regina Sparks reporting for...

07:05.400 --> 07:06.900
(SIGHING)

07:18.400 --> 07:19.400
(CLEARING THROAT)

07:19.500 --> 07:21.300
Hello, there. Hi.

07:22.400 --> 07:24.700
This is Evan Baxter.

07:26.300 --> 07:28.800
Just wanted to say thank you for everything.

07:28.800 --> 07:32.700
Thank you for the new car and for the house.

07:32.700 --> 07:35.700
The house is great. I love it.

07:36.300 --> 07:41.100
I mean, I picked it out,
but you created matter and everything, so...

07:44.300 --> 07:48.100
I just wanted to say that I think
Joan makes a good point,

07:48.200 --> 07:52.700
and that I am now in a position
of great power,

07:52.800 --> 07:56.600
and I know that with great power
comes great responsibility.

07:58.800 --> 08:00.900
So, God,

08:01.000 --> 08:02.000
(CLEARING THROAT)

08:04.800 --> 08:07.200
Please help me change the world.

08:09.100 --> 08:12.000
Okay. That's it. I'm hanging up now.

08:12.900 --> 08:15.400
God bless... Well, you. Okay.

08:31.600 --> 08:33.400
(ALARM RINGING)

08:38.400 --> 08:40.500
What? That's weird.

08:40.600 --> 08:41.600
What?

08:41.700 --> 08:43.299
I set the alarm for 7:00.

08:46.800 --> 08:47.800
(MOTOR WHIRRING)

08:49.900 --> 08:52.000
(GRUNTING)

08:53.300 --> 08:54.300
(SNEEZING)

08:54.400 --> 08:56.000
(GRUNTING)

09:17.500 --> 09:19.500
I am successful. I am powerful.
I am handsome.

09:19.600 --> 09:22.200
I am happy, successful,
powerful, handsome, happy.

09:23.300 --> 09:28.600
All right, everyone, wish me luck.
The Congressman has left the building.

09:28.700 --> 09:33.500
All right, Baxter brood, I will see you
later on this afternoon for the big hike. Yes?

09:33.600 --> 09:34.800
EVAN: You psyched? Are you ready?

09:34.900 --> 09:35.900
ALL: Yeah.

09:36.000 --> 09:37.200
Bye. See you.
Good luck, honey.

09:37.300 --> 09:38.500
Bye, guys!
See you later.

09:38.500 --> 09:39.500
Later, gator.

09:40.500 --> 09:41.500
(EXCLAIMING)

09:41.600 --> 09:42.900
Oh, gosh.

09:42.900 --> 09:45.700
Wow. Honey, did you order anything?

09:46.200 --> 09:48.200
"Alpha and Omega Hardware"?

09:48.200 --> 09:49.200
JOAN: Never heard of them.

09:49.300 --> 09:50.500
Me either.

09:51.200 --> 09:52.900
What do we have?

09:53.200 --> 09:54.300
(GASPING)

09:54.300 --> 09:55.800
What is this stuff?

09:57.400 --> 09:59.000
Must have the wrong address.

09:59.500 --> 10:01.700
Yup. The wrong address.

10:04.500 --> 10:06.500
WOMAN: Congressman Baxter.
Good morning.
Good morning.

10:06.500 --> 10:08.000
MAN 1: Good morning,
Congressman Baxter.
Hello.

10:08.100 --> 10:10.500
MAN 2: Good morning,
Congressman Baxter.
Good morning.

10:10.600 --> 10:13.600
Oh, this is so cool.

10:15.700 --> 10:16.700
Uh-huh.

10:16.800 --> 10:18.600
Yeah. This'll work.

10:18.700 --> 10:22.600
There he is! The head honcho.
The big kahuna.

10:22.700 --> 10:24.600
Rita, I think I have to do the dance.

10:24.700 --> 10:25.900
Do the dance.

10:25.900 --> 10:27.300
(GRUNTING)

10:29.500 --> 10:30.800
That's enough of the dance.

10:30.800 --> 10:33.000
Oh, this is nice! This is really nice!

10:33.100 --> 10:35.700
This is too nice.
There's something crooked going on.

10:35.800 --> 10:37.000
Do you smell anthrax?

10:37.100 --> 10:39.000
Congressman!
Hey, Marty!

10:39.100 --> 10:40.500
Nice sound to that.
I like it.

10:40.600 --> 10:41.500
Here they are!

10:41.600 --> 10:42.600
(ALL CHEERING)

10:42.800 --> 10:43.800
All right.

10:43.900 --> 10:45.600
You remember Sarah, Allen, Michael.

10:45.700 --> 10:48.400
I don't think you know the new kid
Eugene Tennanbaum. I found him at G.W.

10:48.500 --> 10:51.600
Sort of a walking search engine. Watch this.
How many stars on the flag in 1818?

10:51.700 --> 10:52.700
15.

10:52.700 --> 10:54.700
And Congressman Baxter's coffee habits?

10:54.700 --> 10:57.800
He likes a morning latte with a cruller,
a decaf espresso after lunch,

10:57.900 --> 10:59.500
served sans pastry of any kind.

10:59.600 --> 11:02.200
Very impressive. A little freaky,
but I like this kid.

11:02.500 --> 11:03.900
(LAUGHING) I love you.

11:04.900 --> 11:05.900
Hmm?

11:06.400 --> 11:09.900
I mean, we should hang out socially.
I just got a ping-pong table.

11:10.000 --> 11:11.500
Not going to happen.

11:11.600 --> 11:14.800
Go find out where his license plates are.
Everybody else, back to your holes.

11:14.900 --> 11:15.900
EUGENE: He was actually right.

11:16.000 --> 11:17.800
I'm doing a background check on that kid.

11:18.000 --> 11:22.600
Ta-da! This, my friend, is a power office,
to remind you of the mission!

11:22.600 --> 11:24.100
BOTH: "Change the world!"

11:24.100 --> 11:25.900
Okay, Evan, who do you know?
What do you mean?

11:25.900 --> 11:27.900
Oh, come on.
Yesterday we're in the basement.

11:28.000 --> 11:29.800
Today, look at this place.
It's like the Emerald City!

11:29.900 --> 11:33.200
"Enjoy your office.
Your neighbor, Congressman Long."

11:33.200 --> 11:35.500
Congressman Long did this?
Did you say "neighbor"?

11:35.600 --> 11:38.400
That's right. He lives in Prestige Crest,
right up the street.

11:38.500 --> 11:42.300
Evan, you got to tell me these things.
Think of the publicity angle on this!

11:42.400 --> 11:44.800
You and Congressman Long
having a barbecue.

11:44.900 --> 11:46.800
Congressman Long eating your hot dog.

11:46.900 --> 11:48.500
RITA: Hate to break up
your little weenie roast.

11:48.600 --> 11:51.300
Congressman Long's assistant
just dropped this off.

11:51.300 --> 11:52.700
The Congressman would like for you

11:52.800 --> 11:55.000
to junior cosponsor this bill
that he's introducing.

11:55.100 --> 11:59.400
Hold on. Congressman Long asked us to
junior cosponsor his bill? What's the bill?

11:59.500 --> 12:02.100
The Citizens' Integration of Public Lands Act.

12:02.100 --> 12:05.400
Never heard of it. Gene, here, now.
Rita, why didn't you tell me about this?

12:05.500 --> 12:06.600
I just did.

12:06.600 --> 12:08.300
You need to tell me about it
before I need to know about it.

12:08.400 --> 12:10.500
Marty, you are not the vice congressman.
I am the legislative...

12:10.600 --> 12:14.400
Nobody voted for you. If Evan gets shot
in the head, you do not automatically...

12:14.500 --> 12:16.400
If Evan got shot in the head,
you're the first suspect.

12:16.400 --> 12:17.500
Play nice. Play nice.

12:17.600 --> 12:19.600
All right, Eugene, Congressman Long's bill.
What is it?

12:19.700 --> 12:22.700
HR7124, better known as CINPLAN.

12:22.800 --> 12:25.500
The bill would open up fringe areas
of the national parks for development.

12:25.600 --> 12:26.900
Long's been sitting on it for ages...

12:27.000 --> 12:29.100
Got it. Pause. Come on, Evan, this is huge.

12:29.100 --> 12:30.600
You hitch your wagon to the right star,

12:30.600 --> 12:32.900
you could ride all the way down
to Pennsylvania Avenue.

12:32.900 --> 12:34.300
This is day one.

12:34.400 --> 12:36.600
You got your name on a major piece
of legislation!

12:36.600 --> 12:39.600
Oh, and another thing,
he wants you to read it today.

12:39.600 --> 12:41.300
Well, I can't do it today.

12:41.300 --> 12:42.500
I promised my kids...
Eugene.

12:42.600 --> 12:44.500
Well, sir, there's a time clock on the bill.

12:44.500 --> 12:46.600
If Congressman Long wants to
pass it this quarter,

12:46.700 --> 12:48.800
he's going to have to introduce it
to the committee immediately.

12:48.900 --> 12:51.500
I'm personally going with whatever
Congressman Baxter decides,

12:51.600 --> 12:54.500
because if I could be like one man,
it'd be him.

12:54.600 --> 12:55.900
Either him or Kareem.

12:56.000 --> 12:57.100
Can I tase him?

12:57.100 --> 12:58.200
Gene! Heel!

12:58.300 --> 12:59.700
It'd probably be you.

12:59.800 --> 13:03.500
Come on, Evan, this is it!
This is why we came here!

13:03.600 --> 13:05.500
It's world-changing time!

13:05.800 --> 13:07.600
(EXCLAIMING)

13:08.400 --> 13:09.700
Hey, anybody home?

13:09.700 --> 13:11.100
Come on. We're in here!

13:11.100 --> 13:12.900
Hey, guys.

13:12.900 --> 13:16.700
Dad, guess what? I got all your stuff
packed up so that we can...

13:18.100 --> 13:19.200
What's wrong?

13:20.400 --> 13:21.800
We're not going, are we?

13:21.900 --> 13:26.800
First things first.
I have been asked to junior cosponsor a bill.

13:27.500 --> 13:28.500
Yeah.

13:28.600 --> 13:31.000
See? I told you. And you owe me five bucks.

13:31.100 --> 13:32.500
Whoa, whoa, guys.

13:32.600 --> 13:35.400
Hey. Hey, we said we would
have to make sacrifices, right?

13:35.500 --> 13:37.800
DYLAN: Yeah. Whatever.
New house, same old dad.

13:37.900 --> 13:39.900
Hey, I'm the one who has to read this thing!

13:40.000 --> 13:44.300
Hey. Did you hear?
Junior cosponsor of a bill.

13:46.100 --> 13:50.300
Okay, Ry, let's clean all this stuff up.
Dad's got work to do.

14:06.400 --> 14:07.500
(ALARM RINGING)

14:07.600 --> 14:09.900
No. It's 6:14.

14:10.000 --> 14:13.900
Of course. Voodoo clock speaks again.

14:21.400 --> 14:22.500
What the...

14:23.500 --> 14:27.800
Hey! Hey! Hey! No. Okay.

14:27.900 --> 14:30.900
Whoa, whoa! Whoa, whoa! What's going on?

14:31.000 --> 14:33.300
I got a delivery for Evan Baxter!

14:33.300 --> 14:35.200
Yeah, that's not mine. I didn't order that!

14:35.200 --> 14:39.000
I just deliver, guy, huh?
You got a complaint, call the number!

14:39.000 --> 14:43.000
No! Hey! Listen! We are 416, not 614!

14:43.100 --> 14:47.400
You've got the wrong house!
You can't leave that there!

14:47.500 --> 14:50.000
Listen! Listen!

14:50.000 --> 14:52.200
That's going to leave a brown patch!

14:53.000 --> 14:55.100
I am a U.S. Congressman!

14:55.600 --> 14:57.800
(MAN CHATTERING ON TV)

15:04.300 --> 15:05.800
(PHONE RINGING)

15:07.500 --> 15:09.000
Dad, what are you doing? I'm watching this.

15:09.200 --> 15:10.700
Genesis 6:14.

15:14.700 --> 15:16.100
Gen 6:14.

15:16.700 --> 15:18.500
Joan! Do we have a Bible anywhere?

15:27.400 --> 15:28.900
Genesis 6:14.

15:28.900 --> 15:31.400
"Make thee an ark of gopher wood..."

15:32.100 --> 15:33.400
Gopher wood.

15:46.600 --> 15:48.500
GOD: "Go-four-wood." Get it?

15:52.400 --> 15:56.000
Well, it's not really gopher wood.
I just like the wordplay.

15:56.000 --> 15:57.400
No, it's pine and maple.

15:57.500 --> 16:01.000
It was clear-cut from this valley
to make room for all those houses.

16:01.000 --> 16:02.700
Excuse me. Do I know you?

16:02.800 --> 16:04.300
Not as well as I'd like.

16:06.200 --> 16:08.700
I see you got my housewarming gift.

16:08.800 --> 16:11.300
That was you? You sent those?

16:11.400 --> 16:14.000
What are they for? Hey! Hey.

16:14.100 --> 16:16.700
Genesis, chapter six, verse fourteen.

16:17.100 --> 16:18.700
I want you to build an ark.

16:18.800 --> 16:21.100
You want me to build an ark.

16:21.200 --> 16:22.400
Yes.

16:22.400 --> 16:27.500
So that's why the tools.
And you are responsible for the wood?

16:28.500 --> 16:30.600
All right. Well, let's just start over.

16:31.000 --> 16:32.100
(CLEARING THROAT)

16:32.100 --> 16:33.800
