Wow.

35:34.700 --> 35:36.900
What's with the scruffle, mountain man?

35:37.000 --> 35:42.300
Oh, well, you know, I figured it was
a weekend, and I thought...

35:42.400 --> 35:43.500
JOAN: What?

35:43.600 --> 35:44.600
(MUTTERING)

35:44.700 --> 35:45.900
(BOTH GIGGLING)

35:46.000 --> 35:49.300
Honey, did I miss something?
How long have you been growing that?

35:49.400 --> 35:50.400
(DOOR BELL RINGING)

35:50.500 --> 35:51.600
I'll get the door!

35:52.800 --> 35:54.300
Congratulations!

35:54.400 --> 35:55.700
What are you talking about?

35:55.700 --> 35:58.600
The lots. You bought the lots next door!

35:58.700 --> 36:00.600
Hello!

36:01.600 --> 36:02.600
Oh...

36:06.500 --> 36:11.100
And pulling the down payment out of
your home equity? Very gutsy move.

36:11.200 --> 36:13.400
I didn't do that, did I?

36:13.600 --> 36:16.000
You sure did. So what's your plan?
What are you gonna do?

36:16.000 --> 36:18.200
Turn them for a quick profit?
Build them out on spec?

36:20.100 --> 36:23.800
Who wants champagne? Hip, hip hooray!

36:23.900 --> 36:24.900
(EVE WHOOPING)

36:27.000 --> 36:28.400
You bought eight lots?

36:28.500 --> 36:30.900
Yup. I was going to surprise you.

36:32.200 --> 36:35.600
"Surprise, surprise, surprise." Gomer Pyle.

36:36.200 --> 36:37.600
(LAUGHING)

36:37.600 --> 36:40.200
What are you doing?
We can't afford that.

36:40.200 --> 36:42.600
Hey, Mom. John Lennon,
good to see you again.

36:42.700 --> 36:44.300
Good to see you.

36:44.400 --> 36:45.500
(EXHALING)

36:45.600 --> 36:49.200
And eight lots? What are you going to
do with eight lots?

36:50.000 --> 36:52.900
I don't know.
Maybe I'll build a boat.

36:53.000 --> 36:54.800
Did you say "build a boat"?

36:54.900 --> 36:56.700
It might be something fun for the family.

36:56.800 --> 37:00.000
We could take the boat,
go sailing on the lake.

37:01.000 --> 37:03.000
It'd be great in case it floods or something.

37:03.100 --> 37:05.100
What is going on with you?

37:05.600 --> 37:09.300
You bought all those lots
and you're talking about building a boat.

37:09.400 --> 37:11.300
Yeah.
And you grow this crazy beard!

37:11.300 --> 37:12.900
Is this, like, a midlife crisis?

37:13.000 --> 37:14.300
It's not that bad!

37:14.400 --> 37:15.400
It's not?
No.

37:15.500 --> 37:17.300
Why do you think they call it a crisis?

37:17.400 --> 37:18.600
(KIDS CLAMORING)

37:18.700 --> 37:20.600
Hey, keep it down, you guys! Okay?

37:22.400 --> 37:23.800
Oh, my God.

37:23.900 --> 37:25.200
Honey?

37:25.300 --> 37:26.600
Oh, my God.

37:28.000 --> 37:29.000
Honey?

37:29.100 --> 37:30.100
(SNIFFLING)

37:31.100 --> 37:33.100
I know this sounds crazy.

37:34.200 --> 37:36.600
I really think I need to do this.

37:40.200 --> 37:41.400
Okay.

37:42.200 --> 37:43.800
Build your boat.

37:44.900 --> 37:47.300
Just don't take too long, okay?

37:47.400 --> 37:52.600
Because we didn't leave our lives in Buffalo
so you could sail the S.S. Depression.

37:58.300 --> 37:59.300
(THUDDING)

38:12.100 --> 38:13.300
Here we go.

38:13.500 --> 38:17.000
Gentlemen, I'm sure you're all wondering
why I've assembled you here today.

38:17.100 --> 38:19.900
An Argentine lake duck has
a penis as long as its body.

38:19.900 --> 38:21.900
Wow, that's huge. He must be proud.

38:22.000 --> 38:26.200
So, I have come up with a little
construction project for us this weekend.

38:26.300 --> 38:27.400
The whole weekend?

38:27.500 --> 38:28.900
The whole weekend. Yes!

38:29.100 --> 38:30.800
And maybe a couple weekends after that.

38:30.900 --> 38:33.100
I can do this. Help!

38:33.100 --> 38:34.300
(GRUNTING)

38:34.400 --> 38:37.300
How do I stand up with a piece of wood?
Here we go.

38:37.700 --> 38:38.800
(JUST LIKE NOAH'S ARK PLAYING)

38:38.800 --> 38:40.500
Oh, man. Okay, that's good.

38:40.600 --> 38:41.600
(GROANING)

38:42.100 --> 38:45.800
Mother! Father! Sister! Brother! Wow!

38:45.900 --> 38:47.500
EVAN: Keep it straight.

38:48.700 --> 38:49.700
(GRUNTING)

38:50.900 --> 38:52.600
Hey, Dad, he's back!

38:52.900 --> 38:54.400
Ryan, no, don't do...

38:54.500 --> 38:55.500
Ow!

38:56.400 --> 38:59.400
Leverage it up! Leverage. Okay.

38:59.400 --> 39:01.000
Just put some leverage.
You got to put some body weight.

39:01.100 --> 39:03.100
Ready? One, two, three. Come on.

39:03.800 --> 39:04.700
(WOOD SNAPPING)

39:04.900 --> 39:05.800
(EXCLAIMING)

39:06.000 --> 39:07.100
(THUDDING)

39:07.200 --> 39:08.800
Oh, I'm an idiot.

39:08.800 --> 39:12.300
"Nice to meet you, Mr. Congressman.
Why do you have raw beef hands?"

39:12.300 --> 39:14.400
"Well, I'm building an ark."

39:15.700 --> 39:16.800
(GROANING)

39:16.900 --> 39:20.200
I got a boo-boo! I got a boo-boo!
I got a boo-boo!

39:26.000 --> 39:30.900
You ever hear of Home Depot?
Here we go! Here we go! Oh, yeah!

39:31.000 --> 39:32.600
(SCATTING)

39:32.900 --> 39:33.900
(THUDDING)

39:34.500 --> 39:35.400
(GRUNTING)

39:35.600 --> 39:38.100
(GROANING)

39:41.100 --> 39:45.100
All right. So our little Marlboro Man
moment didn't work out so well.

39:45.200 --> 39:48.100
It's a disaster. I don't know
how to build something like this.

39:48.100 --> 39:49.800
That's easy. Just don't.

39:49.800 --> 39:51.600
(EXCLAIMING IN PAIN)

39:54.200 --> 39:55.200
Wow.

39:55.300 --> 39:56.300
(PHONE RINGING)

39:56.800 --> 39:58.100
Hello.

39:58.200 --> 40:01.300
Yes, Marty. Your fearless leader is right here.

40:02.500 --> 40:03.600
Hey, Marty, what's up?

40:13.100 --> 40:15.700
Yes, I'll tell him. Thank you.

40:18.900 --> 40:21.300
I might need security. Thank you.

40:23.900 --> 40:25.200
Can I help you?

40:25.500 --> 40:26.600
Rita, it's me.

40:27.000 --> 40:30.600
Why do you sound like Evan Baxter,
but look like a Bee Gee?

40:30.600 --> 40:32.100
Okay. All right.

40:32.600 --> 40:35.500
Okay, that's great. It's longer.

40:35.500 --> 40:38.400
Oh, my God. It is you.

40:39.000 --> 40:41.100
Evan, what happened?

40:41.200 --> 40:42.300
Did you fall in a mine shaft?

40:42.400 --> 40:43.400
No.

40:43.500 --> 40:44.500
Did you just come out of a coma?

40:44.600 --> 40:45.600
No.

40:45.700 --> 40:47.900
Were you attacked by a werewolf?

40:47.900 --> 40:49.200
No, I wasn't.

40:49.300 --> 40:52.200
Well, if you were going for that rugged look,
you overshot it.

40:52.200 --> 40:53.800
You look like a bum in a suit.

40:53.900 --> 40:56.000
You need Super cuts and a shave.

40:56.100 --> 40:57.400
(EXCLAIMING)

40:57.500 --> 40:59.600
Right! Yeah. But I can't. It doesn't work.

40:59.700 --> 41:01.300
What do you mean, it doesn't work?

41:01.400 --> 41:02.700
It doesn't work!

41:02.800 --> 41:04.500
What? Are you shooting up Rogaine?

41:04.500 --> 41:08.000
Rita, if Evan shows up... I'm sorry, sir.
I'll be with you in just one...

41:09.000 --> 41:10.800
Evan?
Take it in. Take it in.

41:10.900 --> 41:12.600
Okay, yeah, to answer any questions
you may have,

41:12.700 --> 41:14.800
I am going through adult puberty!

41:14.900 --> 41:17.300
This is all temporary.
Why did you bring me down here?

41:17.400 --> 41:18.500
What was so important?

41:18.600 --> 41:20.300
What is so important?

41:20.400 --> 41:23.100
I've got a letter of intent here
about Congressman Long's bill.

41:23.100 --> 41:24.200
You remember that, don't you?

41:24.300 --> 41:27.400
Well, you haven't been here and now
he wants you to sign this in person, Evan!

41:27.400 --> 41:29.700
No, I can't do that. Nope, nope, nope.
Not gonna happen.

41:29.800 --> 41:32.600
No. You can't do that.
Not looking like that. You have to go shave!

41:32.700 --> 41:35.000
I can't shave, Marty.
When I shave, it grows back out.

41:35.100 --> 41:38.000
That happens when you shave!
But then you shave again!

41:38.100 --> 41:39.600
You have no idea.

41:39.600 --> 41:42.600
Evan, what is going on?

41:42.700 --> 41:43.900
I'm...

41:48.400 --> 41:50.200
Building something.

41:51.700 --> 41:53.400
MARTY: You're building something?

41:53.500 --> 41:55.200
Well, I hope it's a barber shop.

41:55.300 --> 41:58.200
Guys, I can't let Long see me
this way, okay?

41:58.200 --> 42:01.400
You're gonna have to tell him I'm sick.
Just cover for me. Just help me out!

42:02.400 --> 42:03.400
(DOOR CLOSING)

42:04.600 --> 42:07.600
Come on, Evan, be reasonable.
You got to get rid of that beard.

42:07.700 --> 42:09.600
I need your face back. I need you back.

42:09.600 --> 42:11.300
Can you at least tell me
what you're building?

42:11.400 --> 42:13.500
I'm building a boat.
You're building a boat?

42:13.500 --> 42:16.200
Look, you got to cover for me.
I don't want anybody to see...

42:16.300 --> 42:18.500
Congressman! There you are!

42:18.600 --> 42:20.600
Congressman Long, I, I, I, I...

42:20.600 --> 42:23.600
Stop stammering, son.
We all play hooky from time to time.

42:23.700 --> 42:27.500
I'm not gonna turn you in to the principal.
Mostly because I am the principal.

42:27.500 --> 42:28.900
(LAUGHING)

42:28.900 --> 42:30.000
Very good.

42:30.000 --> 42:32.500
What's with the veil?
Did you get your new set of braces?

42:32.500 --> 42:36.000
No, no. No. That's hilarious, though.

42:36.100 --> 42:38.900
Would you drop that thing, son?
I can't understand a word you're saying.

42:48.200 --> 42:50.100
It's a wife thing, sir.

42:50.200 --> 42:51.900
Just trying to spice up the love life.

42:52.900 --> 42:55.300
She's a big Loggins and Messina fan.

42:55.300 --> 42:57.700
Keeping it fresh. Keeping it real.

42:57.700 --> 43:00.400
Would you excuse us for a moment?

43:00.500 --> 43:02.900
The Congressman and I are going to
have a little chat.

43:06.900 --> 43:08.000
Come on.

43:08.100 --> 43:10.300
Nice, isn't it? Politics is dog-eat-dog,

43:10.400 --> 43:13.000
but if you survive, they give you
a bigger den. Have a seat.

43:13.100 --> 43:17.100
So, tell me, Congressman,
are you freaking out on me or what?

43:17.200 --> 43:18.200
No, sir.

43:18.200 --> 43:21.500
Oh, come on, son. I hand you
your first cosponsor ship of a bill,

43:21.600 --> 43:23.900
and when you finally show up
you look like the fifth Beatle.

43:24.000 --> 43:26.300
Now, you expect me to believe
everything is hunky dory?

43:26.400 --> 43:29.200
Well, sir, actually, things have been
a little more dory.

43:29.300 --> 43:33.400
Of course they are. I get it.
You know anything about animals, son?

43:34.600 --> 43:37.600
The Argentine lake duck has a penis
as long as its body.

43:39.700 --> 43:43.600
Although you probably already know that.
Or have heard it. Not experienced it.

43:43.600 --> 43:45.800
You ever heard of the Arctic white wolf?

43:45.800 --> 43:46.900
No, sir.

43:46.900 --> 43:48.000
Top of the food chain.

43:48.100 --> 43:50.800
It's fast, it's smart, can fend for itself,
but it chooses not to.

43:50.900 --> 43:52.400
It chooses to run with a pack.

43:52.500 --> 43:53.600
And do you know why?

43:53.600 --> 43:54.600
No.

43:54.700 --> 43:57.200
The Arctic white wolf,
Congressman, realizes

43:57.300 --> 43:59.000
that it is stronger as part of a group.

43:59.100 --> 44:02.100
Do you know what happens when one of
these wolves decides to fend for itself?

44:02.100 --> 44:04.900
The pack kills the loner
for the greater good of the community.

44:05.000 --> 44:06.700
Ouch, that hurts.

44:06.700 --> 44:10.000
Are you familiar with Jim Jenkins,
the junior congressman from Tennessee?

44:10.100 --> 44:13.500
When I met Congressman Jenkins,
he was fresh off the turnip truck,

44:13.600 --> 44:15.700
but now he's sitting on his own committee.

44:15.800 --> 44:18.900
Congressman Jenkins, Congressman
Whitehall, Congressman Freeman,

44:19.000 --> 44:22.700
they all have committee chairs
because they all run with the pack.

44:22.800 --> 44:24.900
Now, you have to come to a decision.

44:25.000 --> 44:27.200
Are you gonna run with the pack
or are you gonna lone wolf it?

44:27.300 --> 44:29.400
I am a pack man, sir.

44:29.500 --> 44:33.600
Good. I'm introducing the CINPLAN bill
in 2 weeks. C-SPAN is covering it live.

44:33.700 --> 44:35.800
I want your full support and nothing else.

44:35.900 --> 44:37.000
Yes, sir.

44:38.000 --> 44:40.200
Those fish are on you like bait on a hook.

44:42.200 --> 44:43.800
Birds follow you.

44:44.700 --> 44:46.400
Fish follow you.

44:50.100 --> 44:53.300
Let's see if we can get
some congressmen to follow you.

44:53.300 --> 44:55.400
Let's get this bill passed,
shall we, Congressman?

44:55.500 --> 44:56.600
Yes, sir.

44:58.800 --> 45:00.400
Hey, fleabag, out of the way.

45:00.500 --> 45:02.500
Hey, Dad, I think there are more
animals than yesterday.

45:02.500 --> 45:04.700
Well, let's not keep
our audience waiting, shall we?

45:05.000 --> 45:06.400
(MOOING)

45:06.500 --> 45:07.800
(SNORTING)

45:07.800 --> 45:12.100
Up, up. Push it up. Push it.
We got it. We got it. Oh, yeah, yeah.

45:12.900 --> 45:15.600
Come on. Just let it go, just let it go.

45:19.100 --> 45:21.500
Dad, we can do this,
but we're gonna need some help.

45:21.600 --> 45:24.800
I know. We just need something
to lift those beams.

45:24.900 --> 45:25.900
(SIGHING)

45:27.100 --> 45:28.600
Like that?

45:28.700 --> 45:30.300
RYAN: Holy moly!

45:30.300 --> 45:31.300
(RYAN CHUCKLING)

45:31.500 --> 45:34.000
RYAN: This is so totally awesome!

45:34.000 --> 45:35.600
JORDAN: This is perfect.

45:35.600 --> 45:37.100
DYLAN: Dad, there's a note.

45:43.400 --> 45:45.000
Let me see that.

45:47.600 --> 45:49.200
How does it work?

45:56.800 --> 45:58.700
RYAN: Dad, this is really weird.

45:58.700 --> 46:01.000
Repeat after me, "We are hamsters!"

46:01.100 --> 46:02.700
BOTH: We are hamsters!

46:02.800 --> 46:04.400
Leg power!

46:04.500 --> 46:06.000
BOTH: Leg power!

46:06.800 --> 46:07.800
And it's in!

46:07.800 --> 46:08.800
(WHOOPING)

46:08.900 --> 46:10.000
That's it.

46:10.300 --> 46:12.000
(REVOLUTION PLAYING)

46:12.200 --> 46:15.200
Hey, who has opposable thumbs? Anybody?

46:19.900 --> 46:23.000
You want to try this one?
Make sure it's straight.

46:23.100 --> 46:24.700
RYAN: This is awesome!
JORDAN: This is so cool.

46:24.700 --> 46:26.700
EVAN: Here we go.
RYAN: Oh, my God!

46:27.100 --> 46:30.400
Yeah. Gotta do the dance.
Come on, let's do the dance.

46:31.700 --> 46:33.600
We're doing the dance.
JORDAN: Dylan, come on. Do the dance.

46:33.600 --> 46:35.400
EVAN: Come on, do the dance.
DYLAN: I'm not doing the dance.

46:36.800 --> 46:37.800
(EXCLAIMS)

46:38.000 --> 46:39.000
Ow!

46:39.100 --> 46:40.100
(CHATTERING)

46:40.500 --> 46:41.600
Don't scratch!

46:41.700 --> 46:42.700
Stop it. Come here.

46:42.800 --> 46:46.300
EVAN: Insult to injury!1
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:08,600
SUSAN: And that's the news.

01:08.700 --> 01:13.600
But before we sign off, we'd like
to congratulate our very own Evan Baxter,

01:13.700 --> 01:17.500
who has just been elected
Buffalo's representative to Congress.

01:17.600 --> 01:18.900
And, now, we have a surprise for Evan.

01:19.000 --> 01:20.600
No, you don't.
We do.

01:20.600 --> 01:23.500
Oh, no. I really didn't expect this.

01:23.600 --> 01:25.800
Here's a look back at his run for office.

01:26.200 --> 01:27.600
(PEOPLE CHEERING)

01:28.500 --> 01:29.600
What are we gonna do?

01:29.700 --> 01:31.100
ALL: Change the world!

01:31.200 --> 01:32.200
That's right!

01:32.900 --> 01:34.400
(ALL CHEERING)

01:39.500 --> 01:41.500
ALL: Baxter! Baxter! Baxter!

01:48.500 --> 01:49.500
Hi.

01:49.600 --> 01:51.000
ALL: Baxter! Baxter!

01:51.000 --> 01:52.500
That's right!

01:54.700 --> 01:55.700
(CLEARING THROAT)

01:57.000 --> 02:01.200
I feel like that old Indian
in front of all the garbage.

02:02.700 --> 02:07.700
So, for the last time, this is Evan Baxter
for Eyewitness News. Good night.

02:08.400 --> 02:11.000
(HAVE YOU EVER SEEN THE RAIN PLAYING)

02:24.300 --> 02:27.500
GPS: Huntsville, Virginia.
Prestige Crest, four miles.

02:27.600 --> 02:29.100
What did we do before GPS?

02:29.200 --> 02:30.200
Nothing.

02:30.300 --> 02:32.500
Guys, Dad's very proud of his new car.

02:32.500 --> 02:37.200
Hey, I am proud of my new car.
Look, I'm a politician now.

02:37.200 --> 02:40.100
I'm in the public eye, and as you know,
when you are in the public eye,

02:40.200 --> 02:41.900
image is everything, isn't it?

02:46.900 --> 02:49.800
EVAN: Here it is! Welcome to the good life.

02:49.800 --> 02:53.200
Hey, guys, why the long faces?
We're off on a new adventure!

02:54.200 --> 02:56.400
It's just we're going to miss our friends.

02:56.400 --> 02:58.300
You'll make new friends, better friends.

02:58.300 --> 02:59.500
Yeah, richer friends.

02:59.600 --> 03:03.400
Do not mouth off to me, sir.
I am the boss of you.

03:03.500 --> 03:06.100
And let me tell you something,
you guys are gonna love this place.

03:06.700 --> 03:09.800
And you know what? I think there's
something for our fishermen up there.

03:11.000 --> 03:14.100
EVAN: Baxter family,
this is what's called a scenic vista.

03:14.200 --> 03:18.000
And I don't think the big man himself
could do a better job. Pretty cool, huh?

03:18.100 --> 03:19.900
Hey, Dad, an iguana can stay underwater
for 28 minutes.

03:20.000 --> 03:21.000
What's that?

03:21.100 --> 03:22.900
And a shrimp's heart is in its head.
Really?

03:23.000 --> 03:25.200
Okay, someone's had enough Animal Planet
for one lifetime.

03:25.300 --> 03:27.200
Yeah, let's head out! Come on.
The best is yet to come!

03:29.000 --> 03:31.700
EVAN: Gentlemen, I have saved
the best for last.

03:31.800 --> 03:35.300
Look over to the right.
That is your new home.

03:41.600 --> 03:42.600
RYAN: Whoa!

03:42.700 --> 03:43.900
JORDAN: That's our house?

03:44.000 --> 03:46.000
Uh-huh.
JOAN: I don't remember it being
this big in the brochure.

03:46.100 --> 03:47.400
Was it this big in the brochure?

03:47.500 --> 03:48.700
EVAN: Pretty amazing, isn't it?

03:48.800 --> 03:50.400
There they are!

03:51.900 --> 03:54.000
Is this curb appeal or what?

03:54.100 --> 03:55.600
Here we go!

03:55.700 --> 03:57.200
Honey, I think you're blocking my photo.

03:57.300 --> 03:58.300
Sorry.

03:58.400 --> 04:00.400
All right, everybody! Say "escrow"!

04:00.500 --> 04:02.300
ALL: Escrow!

04:03.500 --> 04:06.200
RYAN: Come on. Come on. Come on.
Come on. Go. Go. Go.

04:06.800 --> 04:08.700
EVAN: Guys, easy.

04:09.100 --> 04:10.600
(CHILDREN EXCLAIMING)

04:11.200 --> 04:12.300
This is our house?

04:12.400 --> 04:13.400
Uh-huh.

04:14.300 --> 04:15.500
MAN: Careful!

04:15.500 --> 04:17.399
JOAN: Honey, be careful!
EVAN: Watch it!

04:17.500 --> 04:18.600
Are you kidding me?

04:18.700 --> 04:19.899
Mom, can we go upstairs?
JOAN: Yep.

04:20.000 --> 04:21.399
And I get my own room, right?
Yep.

04:21.500 --> 04:22.900
(YELLING EXCITEDLY)

04:22.900 --> 04:25.500
Mr. Baxter, could you give us some
direction on these kitchen cabinets?

04:25.600 --> 04:26.600
Sure.

04:26.600 --> 04:31.200
Okay, it's between your maple
and your old-growth Brazilian cherry.

04:31.300 --> 04:33.200
That is nice! Which is best?

04:33.200 --> 04:36.300
Well, if you're not sensitive
to that "save the rainforest" stuff,

04:36.400 --> 04:37.800
you can't beat the Brazilian cherry.

04:37.900 --> 04:39.100
It's 200, 300 years old.

04:39.100 --> 04:40.700
Three hundred years.
Three hundred.

04:40.700 --> 04:42.300
Wow. That is old.

04:42.300 --> 04:44.600
And now you are going to hold my dishes.

04:44.700 --> 04:46.400
That's right. You going with the ch58,000 --> 00:52:01,600
Making lemonade out of lemons.
Pick up your phone! Come on!

52:01.700 --> 52:05.000
LONG: At its heart,
this bill gives private citizens access

52:05.100 --> 52:07.100
to lands they technically already own.

52:07.200 --> 52:08.800
CONGRESSPERSON:
Will the Chairman yield?

52:08.900 --> 52:09.900
Oh, look, there he is.

52:10.000 --> 52:11.200
Yup, yup, I see him.

52:11.200 --> 52:15.200
Access is just a word you're using
to hide what's really going on here.

52:15.200 --> 52:17.800
This is about development,
short and simple.

52:17.900 --> 52:23.000
Evan, what are you doing?
You have a pony tail on your face!

52:23.100 --> 52:25.500
What you gonna do next?
Cornrow your eyebrows?

52:25.500 --> 52:28.200
Development means
the advancement of jobs,

52:28.300 --> 52:31.900
an increase in domestic commerce.
If you happen to like those things,

52:32.000 --> 52:36.300
I invite you to join myself and
my cosponsors, Congressman Dodd,

52:38.500 --> 52:40.500
Congressman Hughes

52:41.800 --> 52:43.500
and Congressman Baxter.

52:46.000 --> 52:47.400
(PEOPLE GASPING)

52:47.900 --> 52:49.400
(ALL MURMURING)

52:56.400 --> 52:57.400
(GASPING)

53:02.200 --> 53:03.900
(PEOPLE LAUGHING)

53:04.800 --> 53:06.800
Did you just do a wardrobe change?

53:06.900 --> 53:09.900
What do you think this is, the Oscars?
You are not Whoopi.

53:10.000 --> 53:11.000
(HAMMER SLAMMING)

53:11.100 --> 53:13.500
LONG: Ladies and gentlemen! Please!

53:13.600 --> 53:14.600
(HAMMER SLAMMING)

53:14.700 --> 53:18.700
Please! Congressman Baxter has a tendency
to embrace the theatrical

53:18.800 --> 53:21.500
in his support of this bill.
Congressman, let me warn you,

53:21.500 --> 53:25.100
you are approximately 10 seconds away
from committee censure.

53:25.200 --> 53:28.400
Oh, no. Hey, would anyone mind
if I close the window?

53:37.000 --> 53:38.300
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

53:40.700 --> 53:41.700
(ROARING)

53:42.500 --> 53:44.100
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

53:44.100 --> 53:45.200
(GROWLING)

53:56.300 --> 53:57.800
(HAMMER SLAMMING)

53:57.900 --> 54:01.700
LONG: Ladies and gentlemen! Please!
These animals are trained!

54:02.200 --> 54:04.000
I've seen this circus act before!

54:04.000 --> 54:07.000
Congressman, I'm sure St. Francis
would be envious.

54:07.100 --> 54:10.700
We, however, are not.
You have five seconds.

54:10.700 --> 54:13.600
You march yourself and your
little animal troupe out of here now

54:13.600 --> 54:15.500
or you will be forcibly removed.

54:15.600 --> 54:17.500
I'm afraid I can't do that, sir.

54:17.600 --> 54:19.000
Congressman!

54:19.100 --> 54:21.300
These animals are not trained.

54:21.400 --> 54:22.700
Congressman!

54:23.600 --> 54:25.100
I think they want me to save them!

54:25.100 --> 54:27.700
Save them from what, Congressman?

54:27.900 --> 54:31.200
Saving the animals, okay.
I can roll with that. That's a good idea.

54:39.000 --> 54:40.000
The flood.

54:40.400 --> 54:42.900
A flood? Rolling out.

54:43.400 --> 54:44.700
CONGRESSPERSON: The flood.

54:44.800 --> 54:46.900
This has been the hottest,
driest summer on record

54:47.000 --> 54:48.700
and you say we're going to have a flood?

54:48.700 --> 54:50.000
When might we expect this?

54:50.100 --> 54:52.200
September 22, midday.

54:52.300 --> 54:53.300
(CROWD CHATTERING)

54:56.100 --> 54:57.600
That's what I was told.

54:57.700 --> 54:59.700
Might I ask who told you?

55:06.600 --> 55:10.400
Not in front of all those people.
Don't say it. Don't say it.

55:15.500 --> 55:16.800
God.

55:17.500 --> 55:18.500
(SOBBING)

55:21.600 --> 55:24.400
God? You talk to God?

55:25.100 --> 55:26.300
Yes.

55:26.400 --> 55:27.600
LONG: And God is talking back?

55:29.200 --> 55:31.400
Yeah. We hung out a little.

55:31.500 --> 55:33.800
Well, time to update the resume.

55:33.800 --> 55:36.200
Congressman, your name is being
removed from this bill.

55:36.300 --> 55:39.800
Obviously, the stresses of this office
have proven too much for you.

55:39.800 --> 55:41.200
Please have the congressman removed.

55:41.300 --> 55:43.100
No. Please! You don't understand!

55:43.200 --> 55:46.000
God commanded me to build an ark!

55:46.100 --> 55:48.700
It's going to rain!
There's going to be a flood!

55:50.100 --> 55:51.600
Remove him now!

55:51.700 --> 55:54.100
We have to prepare ourselves!

55:54.200 --> 55:56.900
I need to finish the ark!

55:56.900 --> 55:58.000
(HAMMER SLAMMING)

55:58.100 --> 55:59.700
Remove him now!

56:06.700 --> 56:08.600
Does this mean we're moving back home?

56:09.600 --> 56:12.300
Home, Canada. One or the other.

56:22.800 --> 56:27.700
Joan? I know you probably saw
what happened, but I can explain.

56:32.000 --> 56:34.600
Take the stuff to the car, guys.
I'll be there in a minute.

56:37.600 --> 56:38.700
Guys?

56:40.400 --> 56:41.400
(DOOR OPENING)

56:42.300 --> 56:47.400
I'm gonna take them to my mother's.
Evan, I think you need help.

56:48.000 --> 56:52.800
Joan, please. I'm not doing this.
It's not me. It's him.

56:52.800 --> 56:56.200
I went to that meeting in a suit,
and he took it off of me.

56:56.200 --> 57:00.000
Those animals are following me
because of him.

57:00.100 --> 57:03.700
God? Does God know
he's destroying our lives?

57:03.800 --> 57:06.300
Does God know he's going to get you fired?

57:06.400 --> 57:08.200
Yeah! He's trying to get me fired!

57:09.000 --> 57:12.100
He is trying to get me fired!

57:12.200 --> 57:14.400
That way I'll have more time
to work on the ark!

57:14.400 --> 57:16.900
Because the rain and the floods are coming.

57:17.000 --> 57:20.500
No, I heard you, Evan.
The whole world heard you.

57:20.500 --> 57:23.200
Joan, please, you gotta believe me.

57:23.300 --> 57:24.400
(DRIZZLING)

57:25.600 --> 57:30.400
There it is! It's happening!
It's happening! It's raining!

57:47.900 --> 57:49.100
Goodbye, Evan.

57:51.100 --> 57:52.000
(ENGINE STARTING)

57:52.800 --> 57:53.900
Joan!

58:02.700 --> 58:07.200
I know! I know. Whatever you do,
you do because you love me!

58:15.000 --> 58:17.800
Do me a favor. Love me less.

58:19.200 --> 58:20.300
REPORTER: Congressman!

58:20.300 --> 58:23.300
WOMAN: Are you concerned at all
about Congressman Baxter's tirade

58:23.400 --> 58:25.000
and the adverse effects
it may have on your bill?

58:25.100 --> 58:28.900
The day it rains and floods and
Congressman Baxter takes a ride on his ark,

58:29.000 --> 58:31.000
that'll be the day
I'll be concerned. Thank you.

58:31.100 --> 58:33.500
(WAITING ON THE WORLD
TO CHANGE PLAYING)

58:35.000 --> 58:36.000
(BLEATING)

58:36.100 --> 58:40.400
His name is Evan Baxter,
but now he goes by "New York's Noah,"

58:40.500 --> 58:44.200
"Heaven's Evan,"
"The Weirdo with a Beardo."

58:49.100 --> 58:52.800
Okay, guys. Watch it. Watch it.
Coming through. Watch your back.

58:54.400 --> 58:58.100
Marty, will you comment on Congressman
Baxter's change of appearance?

58:58.400 --> 59:02.300
Yes, his hair is long.
Yes, his beard is unshaven.

59:02.400 --> 59:04.600
Are you equally stunned
by this man's appearance?

59:11.000 --> 59:12.200
The way things go around here,

59:12.200 --> 59:15.000
if he gets any crazier,
we may end up in the White House.

59:15.400 --> 59:20.900
(REPORTER SPEAKING SPANISH)

59:21.300 --> 59:24.000
Hey! No, no, no! That's my cup!

59:25.600 --> 59:26.900
Whatever.

59:47.700 --> 59:51.200
He's filling the boat with
two of every kind of animal.

59:51.300 --> 59:54.700
Still to be collected,
two giraffes, two elephants

59:55.700 --> 59:57.300
and one more jackass.

01:00:00.600 --> 01:00:01.700
What an idiot.

01:00:01.700 --> 01:00:03.200
He's a mook.

01:00:03.300 --> 01:00:04.500
Jerks.

01:00:05.500 --> 01:00:08.100
Don't worry about it, you guys.
Come on, eat up.

01:00:08.200 --> 01:00:09.200
Not hungry.

01:00:09.300 --> 01:00:10.400
Yeah, me neither.

01:00:10.500 --> 01:00:12.800
You guys can't eat. I can't stop.

01:00:12.900 --> 01:00:14.800
Can I go to the bathroom?
Me, too?

01:00:14.900 --> 01:00:17.500
Okay. Dylan, go with them. Please?

01:00:17.600 --> 01:00:18.800
Fine.

01:00:21.500 --> 01:00:23.500
Excuse me. Can I get a refill, please?

01:00:24.200 --> 01:00:25.300
Coming right up.

01:00:26.200 --> 01:00:27.200
Thank you.

01:00:27.300 --> 01:00:29.000
Excuse me. Are you all right?

01:00:29.900 --> 01:00:30.900
Yeah.

01:00:32.700 --> 01:00:35.000
No. It's a long story.

01:00:35.100 --> 01:00:36.200
Well, I like stories.

01:00:37.000 --> 01:00:40.000
I'm considered a bit of a storyteller myself.

01:00:41.100 --> 01:00:43.700
My husband...
Have you heard of "New York's Noah"?

01:00:45.800 --> 01:00:47.500
The guy who's building the ark.

01:00:47.600 --> 01:00:48.900
That's him.

01:00:49.000 --> 01:00:52.100
I love that story, Noah and the Ark.

01:00:52.200 --> 01:00:53.800
You know, a lot of people miss
the point of that story.

01:00:53.900 --> 01:00:55.900
They think it's about God's wrath and anger.

01:00:56.800 --> 01:00:58.600
They love it when God gets angry.

01:00:58.600 --> 01:01:01.100
What is the story about, then? The ark?

01:01:01.200 --> 01:01:06.600
Well, I think it's a love story
about believing in each other.

01:01:06.600 --> 01:01:12.300
You know, the animals showed up in pairs.
They stood by each other, side by side,

01:01:12.400 --> 01:01:16.700
just like Noah and his family.
Everybody entered the ark side by side.

01:01:17.800 --> 01:01:20.700
But my husband says God told him to do it.

01:01:22.500 --> 01:01:24.100
What do you do with that?

01:01:24.200 --> 01:01:26.000
Sounds like an opportunity.

01:01:29.000 --> 01:01:30.300
Let me ask you something.

01:01:31.300 --> 01:01:34.500
If someone prays for patience,
you think God gives them patience?

01:01:35.100 --> 01:01:38.400
Or does he give them
the opportunity to be patient?

01:01:40.100 --> 01:01:42.200
If they pray for courage,
does God give them courage,

01:01:42.200 --> 01:01:44.900
or does he give them opportunities
to be courageous?

01:01:47.100 --> 01:01:49.500
If someone prayed
for their family to be closer,

01:01:50.700 --> 01:01:53.600
you think God zaps them
with warm, fuzzy feelings?

01:01:54.500 --> 01:01:56.900
Or does he give them opportunities
to love each other?

01:01:58.800 --> 01:02:00.000
(GASPS QUIETLY)

01:02:00.100 --> 01:02:04.200
Well, I got to run.
A lot of people to serve. Enjoy.

01:02:11.200 --> 01:02:14.200
JON: Guess this comes as no surprise to
those who remember his campaign promise,

01:02:14.300 --> 01:02:16.100
"I will lower taxes,

01:02:16.500 --> 01:02:18.700
"go crazy and build a gigantic ark."

01:02:18.800 --> 01:02:19.600
(PEOPLE LAUGHING)

01:02:26.800 --> 01:02:28.800
JOAN: Oh, my gosh.

01:02:33.400 --> 01:02:34.400
JOAN: Evan!

01:02:34.500 --> 01:02:35.600
Dad?

01:02:35.700 --> 01:02:36.800
Honey!

01:02:36.900 --> 01:02:37.900
Dad?

01:02:37.900 --> 01:02:39.700
You guys, I'm up here.

01:02:55.400 --> 01:02:56.400
(LAUGHING)

01:02:56.900 --> 01:02:58.900
Rough week?
JORDAN: You look really funny.

01:02:59.000 --> 01:03:00.200
You look really old.

01:03:00.300 --> 01:03:01.800
Yeah, well, he is really old.

01:03:04.000 --> 01:03:05.200
Why'd you come back?

01:03:05.300 --> 01:03:06.400
It was the kids.

01:03:06.500 --> 01:03:07.600
Tell him, guys.

01:03:07.700 --> 01:03:09.700
We like you better as the crazy guy.

01:03:09.700 --> 01:03:12.100
You spend time with us
and you're home a lot more.

01:03:12.200 --> 01:03:14.800
Just, please don't make us do
the dance anymore.

01:03:36.400 --> 01:03:40.900
I don't know what's going on,
or what you're going through,

01:03:41.600 --> 01:03:43.400
but we got into this as a family

01:03:44.600 --> 01:03:47.300
and we're gonna get out of it as a family,

01:03:48.200 --> 01:03:49.800
side by side.

01:03:57.300 --> 01:04:00.700
But, Evan, we have to talk about the ark.
It has to come down.

01:04:00.800 --> 01:04:02.100
I can't do that.

01:04:02.200 --> 01:04:03.600
You don't have a choice.

01:04:04.000 --> 01:04:07.600
JOAN: Congressman Long went to the city.
There's a laundry list of code violations.

01:04:07.600 --> 01:04:10.100
You have until September 22
to take it down,

01:04:10.100 --> 01:04:12.000
or they'll take it down and arrest you.

01:04:12.100 --> 01:04:14.100
September 22. That's the day of the flood.

01:04:14.200 --> 01:04:15.700
Mom! Dad! Come here!

01:04:22.000 --> 01:04:24.300
(ANIMALS CALLING)

01:04:40.800 --> 01:04:43.200
Don't you dare take that ark down.

01:04:45.800 --> 01:04:47.700
How are we gonna do this?

01:04:47.800 --> 01:04:50.000
There's no way the five
of us can finish on time.

01:04:50.100 --> 01:04:52.200
We don't have money to hire anybody else.

01:04:52.200 --> 01:04:53.500
(ALPACA CRYING)

01:04:57.300 --> 01:04:59.200
Is that a llama with a hammer?

01:04:59.300 --> 01:05:02.800
An alpaca. They rarely spit at people
unless frightened or abused.

01:05:05.300 --> 01:05:06.500
Let's finish this sucker.

01:05:08.600 --> 01:05:09.600
(READY FOR A MIRACLE PLAYING)

01:05:10.700 --> 01:05:11.700
(ELEPHANT TRUMPETING)

01:05:11.800 --> 01:05:13.000
Come on, let's go.

01:05:13.000 --> 01:05:14.400
WOMAN: No one knows
where they came from

01:05:14.500 --> 01:05:16.300
or how the congressman
is getting them to do it,

01:05:16.400 --> 01:05:22.300
but, two by two, animals of all kinds
are working with Godspeed to build this ark.

01:05:22.400 --> 01:05:23.900
Thank you.

01:05:24.000 --> 01:05:27.200
If this flood really does happen,
"Evan help us."

01:05:28.800 --> 01:05:30.300
Hey! A little help?

01:05:34.300 --> 01:05:35.300
Thanks.

01:05:36.700 --> 01:05:37.800
JOAN: Here it is, hon.

01:05:38.100 --> 01:05:39.000
(MONKEY GIBBERING)

01:05:39.100 --> 01:05:41.800
Perfect. Thanks.

01:05:45.800 --> 01:05:47.300
Hold it right there.

01:05:47.400 --> 01:05:51.000
This is Ed Carson coming to you
live from New York Noah's construction site,

01:05:51.000 --> 01:05:56.100
where we are unable to leave the news van
due to hazardous conditions outside.

01:05:59.300 --> 01:06:00.300
High five.
High five.

01:06:00.300 --> 01:06:01.300
Good job.

01:06:02.000 --> 01:06:03.700
Hey, putty tat.

01:06:06.000 --> 01:06:07.700
(SHRIEKING)

01:06:07.700 --> 01:06:10.600
Go, go, go! He tried to eat me!

01:06:10.900 --> 01:06:13.600
Dylan! Jordan! Check it out!
Your mom's building an ark!

01:06:13.700 --> 01:06:15.000
Let's do the dance.

01:06:15.100 --> 01:06:17.100
JOAN: No, please, No.

01:06:18.700 --> 01:06:19.700
(HONKING)

01:06:19.800 --> 01:06:21.700
WOMAN 1: Well, where did
the animals come from, then?

01:06:21.800 --> 01:06:22.900
WOMAN 2: Please. It's a trick.

01:06:23.000 --> 01:06:24.400
WOMAN 3: It's a circus is what it is.

01:06:24.500 --> 01:06:27.600
Wild animals running amok
in suburban Virginia.

01:06:27.600 --> 01:06:31.300
With all these species,
what's being done about the feces?

01:06:37.400 --> 01:06:42.700
Evan Baxter! You have gone from newsman
to congressman to caveman.

01:06:42.800 --> 01:06:45.300
What makes you so sure God chose you?

01:06:46.600 --> 01:06:48.300
He chose all of us.

01:06:57.700 --> 01:06:59.600
Time to wash up, you guys.

01:07:06.200 --> 01:07:07.400
Thanks.

01:07:10.800 --> 01:07:12.300
You want some?

01:07:32.600 --> 01:07:35.700
RITA: Why couldn't the man
just buy a Corvette?

01:07:35.800 --> 01:07:40.000
Well, well, well. There they are.
It is good to see you guys.

01:07:40.100 --> 01:07:45.100
It's good to see you! Your hair looks great.
It's very regal. Man, I love your hair!

01:07:45.200 --> 01:07:46.600
And you're still sucking up.

01:07:46.700 --> 01:07:47.700
So, why are you here?

01:07:47.800 --> 01:07:48.900
Long locked us out.

01:07:49.000 --> 01:07:50.000
He can't do that.

01:07:50.100 --> 01:07:52.300
I mean, I've been suspended,
but I'm still a congressman.

01:07:52.400 --> 01:07:53.500
Rita, tell him what you know.

01:07:53.600 --> 01:07:54.600
Tell me what?

01:07:54.700 --> 01:07:57.500
I smelled a rat the second
we got that office.

01:07:57.600 --> 01:07:59.600
You don't get an office
like that for nothing.

01:07:59.700 --> 01:08:02.900
So I had the stalker here
do some research.

01:08:02.900 --> 01:08:04.100
Okay, Eugene, talk.

01:08:04.500 --> 01:08:06.300
Prestige Crest used to be federal lands,

01:08:06.400 --> 01:08:09.300
but what's interesting is
how it got into private hands.

01:08:09.300 --> 01:08:11.700
Congressman Long got the approval
to build a dam

01:08:11.800 --> 01:08:14.700
and then passed out the surrounding lands
to a group of private investors.

01:08:14.800 --> 01:08:16.100
Now, the locals fought this thing for years.

01:08:16.200 --> 01:08:18.399
They said Long and his developer buddies
were cutting corners,

01:08:18.500 --> 01:08:20.800
like skipping important
building code checkpoints.

01:08:20.800 --> 01:08:23.899
And with the land use bill, he's gonna do
the same thing with the national parks.

01:08:24.000 --> 01:08:27.700
So, you stand by and shake your pom-poms
while Long and his buddies get rich.

01:08:27.800 --> 01:08:29.899
What can we do? I'm suspended.

01:08:30.000 --> 01:08:33.399
Go back to the Hill and show them
that you can and will fight this bill.

01:08:33.500 --> 01:08:36.500
You guys, I'm sorry. I can't do that.
I have to get back to the ark.

01:08:36.500 --> 01:08:38.200
The ark? All right. Okay.

01:08:38.300 --> 01:08:40.200
God told you to build an ark?
Yes.

01:08:40.300 --> 01:08:43.300
But did he tell you to make your friends
believe in you and follow you here

01:08:43.399 --> 01:08:46.500
so you can make us look stupid?
'Cause I go to church every Sunday.

01:08:47.700 --> 01:08:49.000
Okay, every other Sunday.

01:08:50.000 --> 01:08:53.500
I've been to church!
And that does not sound
like God to me.

01:08:53.600 --> 01:08:56.000
Rita, I know that this
doesn't make any sense.

01:08:56.000 --> 01:08:58.700
I just want you to trust me.
You just have to have faith.

01:08:58.800 --> 01:09:03.399
Evan, faith will not fight this bill.
The CINPLAN vote is today!

01:09:03.500 --> 01:09:07.300
If we're going to stop this thing,
you need to get down to Capitol Hill now!

01:09:07.300 --> 01:09:08.700
Otherwise, it's impossible!

01:09:08.800 --> 01:09:11.600
Dad, Dad, I think it's done.

01:10:10.200 --> 01:10:14.400
What in the world?
I can't even get my cat to
use the litter box.

01:10:55.800 --> 01:11:00.300
It's September 22, and
we're all still here.

01:11:00.300 --> 01:11:01.600
Awkward!

01:11:01.900 --> 01:11:05.300
People! The flood is imminent!

01:11:05.400 --> 01:11:09.000
Board the ark! Save yourselves!

01:11:09.100 --> 01:11:10.500
MAN: Get down, you fool!

01:11:11.000 --> 01:11:15.000
Listen to me!
The time has come!

01:11:15.100 --> 01:11:19.200
No, Captain Ahab!
Your time has come!

01:11:19.200 --> 01:11:20.400
(ALL LAUGHING)

01:11:20.500 --> 01:11:25.200
Yeah, Baxter! The weather's 70 and sunny
with a chance of crazy!

01:11:25.300 --> 01:11:26.700
(ALL GIGGLING)

01:11:28.400 --> 01:11:30.500
(RUMBLING)

01:11:30.600 --> 01:11:34.800
Do you hear that?
The rains are upon us!

01:11:34.900 --> 01:11:36.600
Dad, I don't think that's the rains.

01:11:37.900 --> 01:11:39.100
(SIREN BLARING)

01:11:41.000 --> 01:11:43.700
MAN: Hey, Baxter! Kiss your ark goodbye!

01:11:56.100 --> 01:11:57.200
Where is he?

01:11:57.200 --> 01:11:58.300
On the boat, sir.

01:11:59.300 --> 01:12:01.400
Give me a minute.
Lets see if I can convince "Noah"

01:12:01.500 --> 01:12:03.300
that the world doesn't have to end today.

01:12:07.400 --> 01:12:10.400
I gotta hand it to you,
this is quite the show.

01:12:10.500 --> 01:12:13.500
According to my source,
the show hasn't even started yet.

01:12:13.600 --> 01:12:15.300
Still expecting the big flood.

01:12:15.300 --> 01:12:17.600
You know, voters don't respond
to the gloom and doom stuff.

01:12:17.700 --> 01:12:19.200
They like a more positive message.

01:12:19.200 --> 01:12:20.800
Like the one you're sending with your bill?

01:12:20.900 --> 01:12:22.900
How much did you make off of all this land?

01:12:23.000 --> 01:12:26.300
You are destroying
our national parks for profit.

01:12:26.300 --> 01:12:28.200
You have a problem with somebody
taking a little profit?

01:12:28.300 --> 01:12:29.800
It's called business, son.

01:12:29.900 --> 01:12:32.400
So if I need to get a message out there,
or get a congressman elected

01:12:32.500 --> 01:12:36.500
there are people who pay for it, and yes,
those people want this bill to happen

01:12:36.600 --> 01:12:40.100
and, by God, it's gonna happen.
Now you look down there.

01:12:41.200 --> 01:12:43.000
Those are the wolves, son.

01:12:43.000 --> 01:12:46.200
I'm gonna give you one last chance.
Take down this boat.

01:12:46.200 --> 01:12:50.000
I'm giving you one last chance. Repent.

01:12:51.300 --> 01:12:55.200
Such a shame. You had possibilities.

01:12:55.300 --> 01:12:59.100
But you want to stop progress
to save the Earth. Go for it.

01:12:59.200 --> 01:13:01.400
Good luck getting a tree
to come to the polls.

01:13:07.100 --> 01:13:08.600
Take it down.

01:13:15.900 --> 01:13:19.100
This is a court order approving
the demolition of this boat!

01:13:19.200 --> 01:13:22.200
Evacuate immediately!
You have three minutes!

01:13:24.900 --> 01:13:29.100
Honey. We have to go.
They're going to destroy the boat.

01:13:29.900 --> 01:13:31.000
No.

01:13:32.100 --> 01:13:33.500
It can't end this way.

01:13:35.300 --> 01:13:39.300
Is it too much to ask
for a little precipitation?

01:13:40.500 --> 01:13:44.200
Honey, maybe God didn't mean
a literal flood.

01:13:44.300 --> 01:13:49.600
Maybe he meant a flood of knowledge
or emotion or awareness.

01:13:49.700 --> 01:13:51.300
If that's true,

01:13:52.200 --> 01:13:55.400
I am going to be so pissed.

01:13:55.500 --> 01:13:56.800
Two minutes!

01:13:56.800 --> 01:14:00.300
Get off the boat now
or you will be removed by force.

01:14:00.400 --> 01:14:03.900
Evan, you did it. You built the ark.

01:14:04.000 --> 01:14:05.400
That's all you were asked to do, right?

01:14:05.400 --> 01:14:06.500
No.

01:14:07.000 --> 01:14:11.200
There's something else.
Something's going to happen.
I can feel it.

01:14:11.300 --> 01:14:14.100
Yeah, what's gonna happen is
tear gas and a wrecking ball.

01:14:14.200 --> 01:14:16.200
Evan, think of the kids.

01:14:17.300 --> 01:14:18.700
One minute!

01:14:20.900 --> 01:14:23.000
Dad, whatever you say, I'm with you.

01:14:23.000 --> 01:14:24.500
Yeah, me, too.

01:14:24.600 --> 01:14:26.700
Me, too. But can we keep
some of the animals?

01:14:26.700 --> 01:14:29.000
I like the alpaca. He spits.

01:14:33.500 --> 01:14:36.800
You're right. We did it. We built the boat.

01:14:37.200 --> 01:14:38.200
Yeah.

01:14:39.200 --> 01:14:41.600
Let's go. Let's go, guys. Come on.

01:14:54.700 --> 01:14:56.400
EVAN: Well, I guess they don't want to go.

01:14:56.500 --> 01:14:57.900
It's their instinct.

01:14:58.000 --> 01:14:59.600
What do you mean, hon?

01:14:59.700 --> 01:15:04.400
Some animals know when weather's coming.
When they feel it coming, they sit.

01:15:10.300 --> 01:15:11.800
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

01:15:12.600 --> 01:15:13.700
Joan!

01:15:17.000 --> 01:15:18.400
(THUNDER CLAPPING)

01:15:23.100 --> 01:15:25.600
Okay. Time's up! We're coming in!

01:15:25.700 --> 01:15:28.900
Get that ball in position!
We're clearing them out!

01:15:35.700 --> 01:15:37.600
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

01:15:39.900 --> 01:15:43.200
Is that rain?
It's raining.

01:15:43.200 --> 01:15:45.700
Lucky guess, Baxter. Lucky guess.

01:15:47.300 --> 01:15:48.200
(THUNDER CLAPPING)

01:16:04.100 --> 01:16:06.500
Looks like the drought's finally over.
Good news, eh, Congressman?

01:16:06.600 --> 01:16:08.800
Yeah. Good news.

01:16:11.300 --> 01:16:16.800
Everybody! Please! Get on the ark!

01:16:18.800 --> 01:16:20.300
Go to the car!

01:16:20.400 --> 01:16:24.500
Please! Everyone! On the ark!

01:16:24.600 --> 01:16:27.900
Cover me up! Keep me dry!
Cover me up! Keep me dry!

01:16:28.000 --> 01:16:32.000
Who's crazy now, huh?
Look at us all squishing!

01:16:40.100 --> 01:16:41.800
It kind of stopped raining.

01:16:41.900 --> 01:16:43.000
Is that it?

01:16:43.000 --> 01:16:45.500
What did I tell you? It's fine. It's over.

01:16:45.600 --> 01:16:47.500
Hey, Ahab! This is it?

01:16:48.300 --> 01:16:50.800
Your God experiencing
a little water shortage?

01:16:50.900 --> 01:16:51.900
(ALL LAUGHING)

01:16:52.000 --> 01:16:55.700
It would appear Evan Baxter
was right about the rain,

01:16:55.700 --> 01:16:59.200
with a slight miscalculation
as to the quantity.

01:17:03.300 --> 01:17:04.900
Something's wrong.

01:17:04.900 --> 01:17:06.500
Honey, the clouds are moving away.

01:17:06.600 --> 01:17:09.600
No, no. No, this isn't right.

01:17:10.400 --> 01:17:13.800
Evan, even if it kept raining,
it's not like it could cause a flood in a day.

01:17:13.900 --> 01:17:19.100
But today is the day! It has to be.
This just doesn't make any sense!

01:17:21.100 --> 01:17:22.200
Wait a second.

01:17:22.300 --> 01:17:23.300
What is it?

01:17:23.400 --> 01:17:27.100
Marty said that Long cut corners,
violated building codes.

01:17:27.200 --> 01:17:28.300
What are you talking about?

01:17:28.400 --> 01:17:29.800
The lake, Long Lake.

01:17:29.900 --> 01:17:33.500
It's named after him.
It's the lake! It's the lake!

01:17:46.900 --> 01:17:48.200
Oh, no.

01:17:50.000 --> 01:17:54.800
Get on the ark!
Everyone, on the ark now!

01:17:54.900 --> 01:17:56.700
I think we should get on the ark.

01:17:56.800 --> 01:17:59.600
I agree. I think we should get on the ark also.

01:17:59.700 --> 01:18:02.700
I'm cold. I'm wet. I'm going home.

01:18:10.300 --> 01:18:12.400
Ladies first! Move!

01:18:20.300 --> 01:18:23.900
Oh, my God. This is happening.
This is really happening.

01:18:25.000 --> 01:18:28.400
Holy... Get everyone on the ark now!

01:18:28.400 --> 01:18:31.100
Get on the ark now! Let's go!
Get on the ark! Let's go!

01:18:31.200 --> 01:18:34.100
Go, go, go! Get on the ark!

01:18:34.100 --> 01:18:35.600
(ALL SCREAMING)

01:18:35.700 --> 01:18:39.800
Go, go, go! On the ark! Go, go, go!

01:18:39.900 --> 01:18:42.400
All right, boys! Let's go! Let's go!

01:18:42.400 --> 01:18:46.000
We're gonna need a bigger boat.
Stay here with the kids.

01:18:55.100 --> 01:18:57.000
Come on, Rita!

01:18:57.000 --> 01:19:01.200
Everyone, up the ramp! Onto the deck!
Come on! Hurry, hurry, hurry!

01:19:01.300 --> 01:19:03.000
Dylan, get back inside! It's too dangerous.

01:19:03.100 --> 01:19:05.100
No, Dad. I told you, I'm with you.

01:19:09.500 --> 01:19:12.300
EVAN: Careful, everyone.
In the ark! In the ark!

01:19:12.400 --> 01:19:14.500
Watch your step!
Up the ramp, everybody!

01:19:22.700 --> 01:19:23.800
Guys, help me with the door!

01:19:23.900 --> 01:19:25.200
Get the door! Get the door!

01:19:32.200 --> 01:19:34.100
(ALL SCREAMING)

01:20:07.900 --> 01:20:09.400
Guys! Guys!

01:20:42.400 --> 01:20:44.100
Everybody hang on!

01:20:54.400 --> 01:20:55.500
(ROARING)

01:20:55.600 --> 01:20:57.800
You guys all right? You okay?

01:20:58.400 --> 01:20:59.900
MAN OVER TV:
There's been a flood at Prestige Crest

01:21:00.000 --> 01:21:02.200
and you're seeing live images
of New York Noah's ark

01:21:02.200 --> 01:21:05.500
caught in the storm surge
and heading towards Memorial Bridge!

01:21:13.300 --> 01:21:14.300
WOMAN: We're going to crash!

01:21:14.400 --> 01:21:15.900
MAN: Turn this thing around!

01:21:16.000 --> 01:21:17.300
MAN 2: We're not gonna make it!

01:21:17.400 --> 01:21:18.800
MAN 3: Save us, Baxter!

01:21:30.500 --> 01:21:35.100
I command thee halt! Stop! Whoa!

01:21:35.200 --> 01:21:36.800
WOMAN: It's not working!

01:21:37.600 --> 01:21:40.400
How about a little help here?

01:21:56.700 --> 01:21:57.700
(SCREAMING)

01:22:24.800 --> 01:22:25.800
(SCREAMING)

01:22:26.200 --> 01:22:28.700
What do you mean there was water damage?
It rained for ten minutes.

01:22:28.800 --> 01:22:30.300
That is not possible.

01:22:39.100 --> 01:22:40.200
(EXCLAIMING)

01:22:40.200 --> 01:22:42.100
I love you guys.
All right.

01:22:42.200 --> 01:22:43.500
Seriously.
Okay, I got it.

01:22:43.500 --> 01:22:44.700
I love you.
Thank you.

01:22:44.700 --> 01:22:46.000
(EAGLE CRYING)

01:23:02.100 --> 01:23:06.700
LONG: All those in favor of the Public Land
Act, please signify by saying, "Aye."

01:23:07.100 --> 01:23:09.000
(CLAMORING)

01:23:13.800 --> 01:23:15.100
Good God!

01:23:24.100 --> 01:23:25.900
(ALL YELLING)

01:23:50.400 --> 01:23:51.900
I think we can walk from here.

01:23:52.300 --> 01:23:53.500
(SIRENS BLARING)

01:24:10.100 --> 01:24:14.700
Hello, Congressman.
Mind if I park my boat here for a little while?

01:24:15.600 --> 01:24:16.600
But how...

01:24:16.700 --> 01:24:17.900
The dam, Congressman.

01:24:18.000 --> 01:24:21.600
Your reservoir ruptured.
Prestige Crest, it's all gone.

01:24:21.600 --> 01:24:23.600
No. They said that couldn't happen.

01:24:25.200 --> 01:24:26.600
I never thought this...

01:24:27.800 --> 01:24:32.700
You. You did this to me.
You set me up, you crazy son of a...

01:24:32.800 --> 01:24:35.900
(MONKEYS SCREECHING)

01:24:36.000 --> 01:24:38.300
Wow. That is disgusting.

01:24:38.800 --> 01:24:40.200
If that comes out your front,

01:24:40.300 --> 01:24:42.600
I don't even want to know
what's coming out the back.

01:24:45.500 --> 01:24:46.900
(SNARLING)

01:24:47.000 --> 01:24:49.500
Don't look down, Congressman,
but the wolves are here,

01:24:49.600 --> 01:24:53.500
although I wouldn't worry so much
about these wolves as those.

01:25:01.800 --> 01:25:03.200
Gesundheit.

01:25:15.300 --> 01:25:18.900
MAN 1: As you can see behind me,
New York Noah's prediction came true.

01:25:19.000 --> 01:25:21.500
WOMAN: The vote of the Land Act Bill
has been suspended,

01:25:21.600 --> 01:25:24.400
pending investigation of
Congressman Long for profiteering...

01:25:24.500 --> 01:25:27.500
MAN 2: Of course now, the question is,
how will these animals be returned

01:25:27.500 --> 01:25:29.100
to their natural habitats?

01:25:29.200 --> 01:25:33.000
Something tells me, if God got them here,
he can probably get them home.

01:25:33.100 --> 01:25:36.200
WOMAN 2: The House will undoubtedly
reinstate Congressman Baxter

01:25:36.200 --> 01:25:38.000
when it reconvenes in the morning.

01:25:38.100 --> 01:25:42.000
Until then, there is a lot to be done
here on Capitol Hill.

01:25:42.000 --> 01:25:43.000
JORDAN: How's Buster doing?

01:25:43.100 --> 01:25:44.100
EVAN: Come on, Buster.

01:25:44.200 --> 01:25:46.600
JOAN: No, come on. Come on!
RYAN: Come on!

01:25:46.700 --> 01:25:48.500
EVAN: These too heavy? It's all right?
JORDAN: No, it's fine.

01:25:48.500 --> 01:25:49.600
RYAN: He can't keep up.

01:25:49.700 --> 01:25:51.000
I know, sweetie!

01:25:51.000 --> 01:25:54.200
All right. What do you say
we take a little break?

01:25:54.300 --> 01:25:55.900
We've only been walking
for, like, five minutes, Dad.

01:25:56.000 --> 01:25:59.200
Well, five on, five off.
Life is about balance, right?

01:25:59.300 --> 01:26:00.600
How about some sandwiches?
Okay.

01:26:00.700 --> 01:26:02.300
Who wants sandwiches?
Let's do it!

01:26:02.400 --> 01:26:03.600
RYAN: I get first dibs!

01:26:03.600 --> 01:26:06.000
Everyone but Buster
is going to get a sandwich.

01:26:06.000 --> 01:26:10.400
You do not get a sandwich!
You're a dog and you do
not get a sandwich!

01:26:10.500 --> 01:26:13.700
Buster is part of the family now.
You're just gonna have to get used to it.

01:26:13.800 --> 01:26:15.600
Poor Buster!

01:26:16.400 --> 01:26:19.500
Honey, come here.
Sweetheart, be careful. Come here.

01:26:19.600 --> 01:26:21.500
Hey, hon, save me one, okay?
Okay.

01:26:21.500 --> 01:26:22.700
I'll be right back.

01:26:31.300 --> 01:26:32.700
Hey.
Hey.

01:26:34.500 --> 01:26:36.000
What are you doing here?

01:26:36.800 --> 01:26:39.200
Just hanging out with some old friends.

01:26:39.300 --> 01:26:42.600
You knew all along, didn't you?
You knew the dam was unstable.

01:26:42.700 --> 01:26:46.500
If it hadn't been for the ark,
my family, the neighbors...

01:26:46.600 --> 01:26:48.800
I fought you every step of the way.

01:26:48.900 --> 01:26:50.400
Yes, but you did it.

01:26:51.400 --> 01:26:56.000
So, you had nothing to do with the flood?
Like where the ark landed exactly?

01:26:56.000 --> 01:26:59.500
I gave you a little shove at the end.
Sue me.

01:26:59.600 --> 01:27:00.600
(BOTH CHUCKLING)

01:27:02.100 --> 01:27:05.800
You did good, son.
You changed the world.

01:27:05.900 --> 01:27:07.300
No, no, I didn't.

01:27:07.400 --> 01:27:08.600
Well, let's see.

01:27:08.600 --> 01:27:12.700
Spending time with your family,
making them very happy.

01:27:12.800 --> 01:27:14.100
Gave that dog a home.

01:27:14.200 --> 01:27:16.100
Right. So?

01:27:16.800 --> 01:27:18.500
So?

01:27:18.500 --> 01:27:20.700
How do we change the world?

01:27:22.200 --> 01:27:25.700
One act of random kindness at a time.

01:27:25.700 --> 01:27:30.300
One act of random kindness.

01:27:30.400 --> 01:27:31.500
EVAN: Wow.

01:27:35.500 --> 01:27:36.800
It's time.

01:27:38.800 --> 01:27:40.300
Do the dance.

01:27:41.800 --> 01:27:43.400
Care to join me?

01:27:49.300 --> 01:27:50.300
(CHUCKLING)

01:28:05.400 --> 01:28:06.400
(DOVE COOING)

01:28:39.900 --> 01:28:42.700
I now issue a new commandment,

01:28:42.700 --> 01:28:44.800
"Thou shalt do the dance."

01:28:44.900 --> 01:28:46.600
(GONNA MAKE YOU SWEAT,
EVERYBODY DANCE NOW PLAYING)

01:29:40.700 --> 01:29:42.200
(LIP-SYNCING)

01:29:46.900 --> 01:29:50.100
Stop it! This is stupid!

01:29:50.200 --> 01:29:53.400
That's awful dancing! You better stop!

01:29:59.200 --> 01:30:18.000
(LIP-SYNCING)

01:30:26.300 --> 01:30:28.000
(PEOPLE CHEERING)

01:30:31.700 --> 01:30:33.800
MAN 1: Ladies and gentlemen,
you don't have to go home.

01:30:33.900 --> 01:30:36.500
You just have to go. We are wrapped.

01:30:36.600 --> 01:30:39.300
MAN 2: We're wrapped.
We love you. Thank you.

